<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
The long racemes with ebracteate flowers and the linear, reflexed calyx lobes are good characters for this species. It is barely distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coccinia barteri" order="Uredinales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Coccinia barteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without flowers. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coccinia keayana" order="Uredinales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keayana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Coccinia keayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collections often have a bluish green tinge and the lobes conspicuously point forwards (see Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 32" captionStartId="F32" captionText="Figure 32. Reconstruction of the habit of Coccinia keayana based on C. C. H. Jongkind et al. 6542 (WAG). Black bar equals 1 cm." pageId="86" pageNumber="87">32</figureCitation>
), which might only rarely occur in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coccinia barteri" order="Uredinales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Coccinia barteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The corolla is rather tubular, sometimes somewhat inflated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="taxonomic remarks">
<paragraph pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Taxonomic remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
The name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coccinia keayana" order="Uredinales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keayana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Coccinia keayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.Fern. is misapplied for the Flora of Cameroon or western Central Africa in general (for details, see taxonomical remarks of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coccinia barteri" order="Uredinales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Coccinia barteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
